WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.135
How about you have dinner
with me?

00:03.137 --> 00:04.470
<i> Previously on "Scandal"...</i>

00:04.472 --> 00:06.038
I'm glad you could get past
your issues with me.

00:06.040 --> 00:08.474
This isn't happening again.

00:08.476 --> 00:10.309
Yes, it is.

00:10.311 --> 00:12.144
We don't want
your stinking education bill.

00:12.146 --> 00:13.846
[ Crowd concurs, applause ]

00:13.848 --> 00:15.047
Vargas: The world is changing,

00:15.049 --> 00:16.548
and we have got to change
with it.

00:16.550 --> 00:19.151
[ Applause ]

00:19.153 --> 00:20.953
[ Laughs ]

00:29.830 --> 00:32.064
Mm. [ Chuckles ]

00:32.066 --> 00:33.632
[ Laughs ]

00:33.634 --> 00:37.202
[ Car door opens ]
Sir, I am so sorry
to disturb you.

00:37.204 --> 00:39.338
Abby...you remember
Lillian Forrester?

00:39.340 --> 00:40.572
Of course.
Hello, Ms. Forrester.

00:40.574 --> 00:42.074
[ Clears throat ]
Hello, Abby.

00:42.076 --> 00:44.076
Sir, if I could just have
a moment of your time

00:44.078 --> 00:46.211
on a very, very urgent matter
of the utmost importance.

00:46.213 --> 00:47.713
This can wait.

00:47.715 --> 00:49.314
No, this won't take long.

00:49.316 --> 00:51.850
It takes as long as it takes.
I'm not mad. I'm fine.

00:51.852 --> 00:53.685
It's kind of sexy, actually.

00:53.687 --> 00:56.055
You're the leader
of the free world.

00:56.057 --> 00:58.023
Hottest excuse
I've ever gotten.

00:58.025 --> 01:00.192
I'm sorry about this.

01:00.194 --> 01:01.727
I'll make it up to you
another night.

01:01.729 --> 01:03.395
You better.

01:05.166 --> 01:06.765
Nice to see you again, Abby.

01:06.767 --> 01:09.101
[ Car door opens, closes ]

01:10.671 --> 01:12.738
[ Sighs ]

01:12.740 --> 01:14.039
Are we at war?

01:14.041 --> 01:16.675
Did California fall
into the ocean?

01:19.380 --> 01:21.180
Abby, speak.

01:21.182 --> 01:23.916
The thing is,
we haven't run the scenarios,

01:23.918 --> 01:26.285
set up the infrastructure,
done any strategic planning.

01:26.287 --> 01:27.886
What in God's name
are you talking about?

01:27.888 --> 01:29.354
You're Wild Carding, sir.

01:29.356 --> 01:31.123
You know what that means.

01:31.125 --> 01:32.558
Please tell me
you know what that means

01:32.560 --> 01:33.959
so I don't have to say
more words.

01:35.529 --> 01:37.629
Of course you don't, because
the universe hates us both.

01:37.631 --> 01:42.267
Okay, so, uh,
the code for when a President

01:42.269 --> 01:44.703
has a female friend
that is not, um, regular,

01:44.705 --> 01:46.872
is called a Wild Card.

01:46.874 --> 01:48.240
And so when you are out
with a woman,

01:48.242 --> 01:50.476
and it seems like
you might...

01:50.478 --> 01:51.610
have a good time,

01:51.612 --> 01:52.711
the guys in the bunker
call it...

01:52.713 --> 01:53.946
-Wild Carding.
-Yeah.

01:53.948 --> 01:55.481
Abby...
This is none of your business.

01:55.483 --> 01:57.416
It is, sir.
Wild Carding is my business.

01:57.418 --> 01:58.984
Look, no judgments.

01:58.986 --> 02:00.452
If you want to spend the night
at her home,

02:00.454 --> 02:03.622
there are protocols --
plans that have to be made.

02:03.624 --> 02:05.157
Secret Service schedules
that need to be adjusted.

02:05.159 --> 02:06.291
Extra drivers booked.

02:06.293 --> 02:08.460
The ambulance has to be
restocked and crewed.

02:08.462 --> 02:10.596
Routes to major trauma centers
have to be plotted

02:10.598 --> 02:13.098
as well as the distances
to Marine One and Air Force One.

02:13.100 --> 02:15.134
The football has to be
in attendance, as does
the mobile command center.

02:15.136 --> 02:17.336
We never did any of this
with Olivia.
We did.

02:17.338 --> 02:19.138
Secret Service
put in an entire unit

02:19.140 --> 02:21.039
in the basement
after Liv's kidnapping.

02:23.010 --> 02:25.244
So I need to make a plan.

02:25.246 --> 02:26.678
I need to put in a request
to get laid?

02:26.680 --> 02:28.113
That's what
you're telling me?

02:28.115 --> 02:29.648
There's some sort of form I need
to fill out to get it on?

02:29.650 --> 02:31.483
I'm telling you that once
you're done having a good time,

02:31.485 --> 02:33.318
a team of specialists
will have to come in

02:33.320 --> 02:34.453
and sweep your date's home

02:34.455 --> 02:36.488
to remove any
and all traces of your DNA.

02:36.490 --> 02:38.824
Stop talking.
Including hair, skin cells,
saliva, and semen.

02:38.826 --> 02:40.125
This is for your safety.
Stop talking.

02:40.127 --> 02:42.828
As you know,
since 2011, 14 countries

02:42.830 --> 02:44.363
have been collecting
the DNA of world leaders

02:44.365 --> 02:46.431
in pursuit of creating
individualized weapons --

02:46.433 --> 02:48.033
Stop. Talking.

02:50.504 --> 02:52.938
Get as far away from me
as you possibly can,

02:52.940 --> 02:54.640
and never
bring this up again.

02:54.642 --> 02:58.477
♪♪

02:58.479 --> 03:00.445
[ Sighs ]

03:03.217 --> 03:04.917
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

03:09.056 --> 03:11.123
There are only two seasons
in Washington,

03:11.125 --> 03:12.791
lovers of liberty --

03:12.793 --> 03:15.661
tax season, a shameful time
when your nation's leaders

03:15.663 --> 03:19.331
rob you blind for their own
amusement and unending sloth --

03:19.333 --> 03:21.533
and election season,
a shameful time

03:21.535 --> 03:24.536
when your nation's leaders
offer you empty platitudes

03:24.538 --> 03:28.207
in exchange for your votes
and your hard-earned cash.

03:28.209 --> 03:30.409
I can smell the change
in the air.

03:30.411 --> 03:33.645
It smells like hair spray
and apple pie and fresh manure,

03:33.647 --> 03:35.480
like America itself.

03:35.482 --> 03:37.716
And, by God,
that must be why I love it.

03:37.718 --> 03:40.519
So let's rejoice,
lovers of liberty.

03:40.521 --> 03:41.820
All the leaves are brown,

03:41.822 --> 03:44.756
but the sun is out,
and the sky is blue.

03:44.758 --> 03:46.058
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

03:47.428 --> 03:51.563
"Lady in Waiting: My Story...
[Laughs] My Turn."

03:51.565 --> 03:52.731
[ Chuckles ]
Good title.

03:52.733 --> 03:54.366
Hmm.

03:54.368 --> 03:56.235
I told you to get yourself
some real power, and you did --

03:56.237 --> 03:58.770
Mellie Grant will be
a formidable candidate.

03:58.772 --> 04:00.839
And more importantly,
you didn't let

04:00.841 --> 04:03.208
your complicated history
with the woman deter you.

04:03.210 --> 04:04.443
You didn't make it
personal.

04:04.445 --> 04:07.746
You saw your chance,
and you pounced.

04:07.748 --> 04:10.382
[ Laughs ]

04:10.384 --> 04:11.917
[ Laughs ]

04:11.919 --> 04:14.620
I do have a request.

04:14.622 --> 04:15.721
I'm listening.

04:15.723 --> 04:17.089
It involves Jake.

04:18.626 --> 04:20.158
I'm still listening.

04:21.528 --> 04:24.062
Well,
Jake isn't built like us.

04:24.064 --> 04:25.764
He's always up
for the fight,

04:25.766 --> 04:28.267
but he doesn't<i> live</i> for it,
not like we do.

04:28.269 --> 04:30.802
The chaos stokes our fire,
it lights our blood.

04:30.804 --> 04:32.304
Jake, on the other hand,

04:32.306 --> 04:35.140
he was practically an orphan
when I brought him in.

04:35.142 --> 04:37.476
What do orphans crave
at heart?

04:37.478 --> 04:39.444
The things they were denied --

04:39.446 --> 04:44.116
family, stability,
the normal life.

04:45.386 --> 04:47.152
He's head of the NSA.
That's not normal.

04:47.154 --> 04:48.954
I'm not talking
about the warrior.

04:48.956 --> 04:50.222
I'm talking about the man.

04:53.327 --> 04:55.927
He's seeing someone.

04:55.929 --> 04:57.262
Someone he likes very much.

04:57.264 --> 04:58.263
It's not like
we're a couple.

04:58.265 --> 05:00.999
Olivia...
Jake is an adult, Dad.

05:01.001 --> 05:02.901
[ Sighs ]

05:06.740 --> 05:08.440
Yeah, you're right.

05:08.442 --> 05:10.909
[ Both chuckle ]

05:10.911 --> 05:12.344
I'm sorry.

05:12.346 --> 05:15.480
I've overstepped...again.

05:15.482 --> 05:18.483
I just want what's best
for both my kids.

05:18.485 --> 05:22.321
[ Sniffs ]

05:22.323 --> 05:25.157
Mellie Grant.

05:25.159 --> 05:26.692
I'm proud of you.

05:26.694 --> 05:29.494
You're drinking
from the chalice now.

05:29.496 --> 05:32.998
♪♪

05:36.270 --> 05:37.936
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

05:37.938 --> 05:40.839
We have to keep fighting
for a better America --

05:40.841 --> 05:43.342
a stronger America.

05:43.344 --> 05:45.777
And I have the experience
and the passion

05:45.779 --> 05:47.112
to lead the fight,

05:47.114 --> 05:49.681
which is why
I'm running to be

05:49.683 --> 05:53.452
<i> the next President of</i>
<i> the United States of America.</i>

05:53.454 --> 05:57.122
[ Cellphone rings ]

05:57.124 --> 05:58.824
Hm.

05:58.826 --> 06:00.726
-Answer it.
-No.

06:00.728 --> 06:02.527
Tell her she was great.
No.

06:02.529 --> 06:04.730
Tell her now.
I'm not answering
that phone.

06:06.734 --> 06:08.333
You were great!

06:08.335 --> 06:10.702
Aw, thank you.
I was so nervous.

06:10.704 --> 06:12.904
Well,
you didn't seem nervous.

06:12.906 --> 06:14.172
It was very presidential.

06:14.174 --> 06:16.842
Thank you.

06:16.844 --> 06:18.810
I wish
I could have been there.

06:18.812 --> 06:20.679
I wish you could have, too.

06:20.681 --> 06:22.414
But...
Yes?

06:22.416 --> 06:25.584
Since you weren't there,
I wanted to see

06:25.586 --> 06:28.920
if maybe you wanted to come over
for dinner tomorrow.

06:28.922 --> 06:31.857
Casey's at her grandma's
for a few days,

06:31.859 --> 06:34.593
so I have the house to myself.

06:34.595 --> 06:36.595
You do?

06:36.597 --> 06:39.131
Yeah.

06:43.771 --> 06:45.437
Maybe it's not
a great idea, huh?

06:45.439 --> 06:47.439
No, no, it is.
I'd love to.

06:47.441 --> 06:48.740
You sure?

06:48.742 --> 06:50.609
Yes, absolutely.

06:50.611 --> 06:52.611
Great. 7:00.

06:52.613 --> 06:54.279
7:00 it is.

06:54.281 --> 06:57.516
What does she want?

06:57.518 --> 06:58.884
She wants to see a movie.

06:58.886 --> 07:02.053
Mm. Adorable.

07:02.055 --> 07:03.989
Turn over.

07:06.860 --> 07:08.727
Busy tonight?
No.

07:08.729 --> 07:10.061
I mean, barring acts of war
and what have you,

07:10.063 --> 07:11.997
I should be free.
Text me.

07:14.201 --> 07:16.134
Hey.
Huck.

07:17.538 --> 07:19.070
You're one creepy bastard,
you know that?

07:19.072 --> 07:20.872
Yes.

07:20.874 --> 07:24.309
♪♪

07:24.311 --> 07:25.610
What are you doing here?

07:25.612 --> 07:26.812
We need to talk.
Can I come in?

07:29.616 --> 07:31.583
What have you found...

07:31.585 --> 07:33.785
on Jake, on Rowan?

07:33.787 --> 07:36.588
Huck, I --
I'd like to believe
that you're collecting intel,

07:36.590 --> 07:38.990
figuring out
what Jake and Rowan are up to.

07:38.992 --> 07:41.426
Otherwise, you're just
sleeping with the enemy,

07:41.428 --> 07:45.163
and the Liv that I know
would never do that.

07:45.165 --> 07:47.732
Jake and my father
aren't up to anything.

07:47.734 --> 07:49.601
Say that again.
Huck.

07:49.603 --> 07:53.138
Say that again so you can hear
how ridiculous it sounds.

07:53.140 --> 07:54.239
Huck,
I think you should --

07:54.241 --> 07:56.308
Jake is living
with your father.

07:56.310 --> 07:58.910
He is still being controlled
by your father.

07:58.912 --> 08:01.313
He killed someone
to become head of the NSA

08:01.315 --> 08:03.348
because your father
told him to do it.

08:03.350 --> 08:05.984
Do you honestly think
that's where it ends?

08:05.986 --> 08:08.286
That your father's finished?

08:08.288 --> 08:10.155
When has that man
ever been finished, Liv?

08:10.157 --> 08:13.158
♪♪

08:14.328 --> 08:18.196
No one
is up to anything, Huck.

08:18.198 --> 08:20.699
There is no intel
to collect.

08:21.668 --> 08:23.134
[ Chuckles lightly ]

08:23.136 --> 08:25.437
When you snap back
to reality

08:25.439 --> 08:27.839
and realize
what's really going on,

08:27.841 --> 08:29.841
you know where to find me.

08:29.843 --> 08:32.811
♪♪

08:32.813 --> 08:36.114
[ Door opens, closes ]

08:36.116 --> 08:38.283
Ethan:
Francisco Vargas.

08:38.285 --> 08:40.185
He was born
in Allentown, Pennsylvania,

08:40.187 --> 08:41.353
and grew up
in Philadelphia.

08:41.355 --> 08:43.288
His parents immigrated
from Mexico.

08:43.290 --> 08:45.357
Mother was a nurse.
Father was an economist.

08:45.359 --> 08:47.459
Has a less successful
younger brother.

08:47.461 --> 08:49.528
Francisco was a great student,
gifted athlete.

08:49.530 --> 08:52.197
After graduation,
he went into the military

08:52.199 --> 08:54.399
and fought
in the first Gulf War.

08:54.401 --> 08:56.701
When he came home, he married
his high-school sweetheart

08:56.703 --> 08:58.303
and enrolled at Penn State.

08:58.305 --> 09:01.072
Okay.

09:01.074 --> 09:03.041
He was elected
to the Philadelphia City Council

09:03.043 --> 09:04.409
when he was 32.

09:04.411 --> 09:06.478
He was mayor at 36,
and two years ago,

09:06.480 --> 09:09.180
he became the first Hispanic
governor of Pennsylvania.

09:09.182 --> 09:11.349
He's pro-choice,
pro-gun, pro-growth,

09:11.351 --> 09:13.184
pro-Earth, pro-science,
pro-religion.

09:13.186 --> 09:15.921
He has a 95% approval rating
with liberals

09:15.923 --> 09:17.489
and 51% from conservatives.

09:17.491 --> 09:19.858
[Chuckles] Somehow, he seems
to appeal to everyone.

09:19.860 --> 09:21.560
He has three kids
in public school.

09:21.562 --> 09:23.528
He effectively manages
his sodium intake.

09:23.530 --> 09:25.931
He plays guitar in a popular
Philly alt-country band,

09:25.933 --> 09:28.333
and he hunts
with a crossbow.

09:30.537 --> 09:32.604
[ Laughs ] Okay.

09:32.606 --> 09:35.006
Now...

09:35.008 --> 09:36.942
Give it to me.

09:38.278 --> 09:39.744
What?
The bad stuff.

09:39.746 --> 09:41.446
The bad stuff.

09:41.448 --> 09:43.582
The dirt!
The corruption!

09:43.584 --> 09:48.053
The sleazy oil deal,
the developer payoff,

09:48.055 --> 09:50.021
the infant son he has
in Chicago

09:50.023 --> 09:52.023
with the girlfriend
he bangs

09:52.025 --> 09:53.959
at the governor's retreat
every year.

09:53.961 --> 09:55.727
The bad stuff!

09:55.729 --> 09:57.696
Come on, give it to me.

09:58.932 --> 10:00.599
There is no bad stuff.

10:00.601 --> 10:02.701
There's bad stuff.
I didn't find any.

10:02.703 --> 10:03.969
Then you just didn't look
hard enough.

10:03.971 --> 10:06.204
No, there isn't any,
because I looked.

10:06.206 --> 10:08.039
And if there was bad stuff,

10:08.041 --> 10:11.943
and I didn't find it,
and you did, then...

10:11.945 --> 10:13.745
This guy's clean.

10:13.747 --> 10:15.981
The only thing bad
about Francisco Vargas

10:15.983 --> 10:17.382
is nobody knows who he is.

10:17.384 --> 10:20.218
He has
no national profile whatsoever.

10:20.220 --> 10:22.153
I'd literally
never even heard of the guy

10:22.155 --> 10:24.289
until you called
and asked me about him.

10:24.291 --> 10:27.225
Why are we looking into
Francisco Vargas anyway?

10:27.227 --> 10:28.994
What was he doing
in the Gulf War?

10:30.464 --> 10:31.830
He was Special Forces.

10:34.601 --> 10:36.568
Special Forces.

10:36.570 --> 10:39.337
♪♪

10:40.641 --> 10:42.874
Goodbye, Ethan.

10:44.911 --> 10:47.679
[ Door opens, closes ]

10:47.681 --> 10:49.014
He's gone.

10:50.684 --> 10:51.983
What was that about?

10:51.985 --> 10:54.419
That?
That was about revolution.

10:54.421 --> 10:55.787
[ Sighs ]

10:55.789 --> 10:57.589
That was about freedom.

10:57.591 --> 11:01.359
That was about liberation.

11:01.361 --> 11:06.131
Years from now, when they open
their history books,

11:06.133 --> 11:07.499
my face will be
what they see,

11:07.501 --> 11:09.434
because everything
that happens next

11:09.436 --> 11:10.935
is going to be signed,
sealed, and delivered

11:10.937 --> 11:12.203
by Cyrus Rutherford Beene.

11:14.474 --> 11:16.841
It's time to go to work.

11:16.843 --> 11:18.643
What kind of work?

11:18.645 --> 11:21.046
We're making the next
President of the United States.

11:22.683 --> 11:24.883
Get dressed.

11:24.885 --> 11:26.084
We have a lot of work to do.

11:30.457 --> 11:31.856
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

11:31.858 --> 11:34.459
Hey, don't say anything about
how big this suitcase is.

11:34.461 --> 11:37.395
I'm going away for the weekend
with my boyfriend.

11:37.397 --> 11:40.031
Like I'm a regular person
with a cat or something.

11:40.033 --> 11:41.399
Okay,
I got us candy, magazines.

11:41.401 --> 11:42.867
I may have overdone it
with the chips,

11:42.869 --> 11:44.235
but we have four hours
on the road,

11:44.237 --> 11:45.704
and I believe in us.

11:45.706 --> 11:47.138
Mm.

11:48.709 --> 11:51.643
Come --

11:51.645 --> 11:53.311
What's wrong?

11:53.313 --> 11:54.879
I just got a call
from an old buddy of mine.

11:54.881 --> 11:58.349
We killed a lot of people
together back in the day. Hmm.

11:58.351 --> 12:00.585
Anyway, his wife's out of town.
He got called in to work.

12:00.587 --> 12:02.554
And he needs me
to watch his kid.

12:02.556 --> 12:05.190
Someone wants<i> you</i>
to babysit?

12:05.192 --> 12:07.158
I probably wasn't
the first call,

12:07.160 --> 12:09.260
but this guy and I,
we've got each other's back.

12:09.262 --> 12:10.862
When I say I'm gonna
kill somebody, I kill somebody.

12:10.864 --> 12:13.264
When I say I'm gonna watch
someone's kid, I watch the kid.

12:13.266 --> 12:14.733
You don't have to come.

12:14.735 --> 12:16.701
And leave you alone
with a child?

12:16.703 --> 12:18.002
[ Scoffs ]
Yeah, I don't think so.

12:24.845 --> 12:27.011
[ Sighs ]

12:29.883 --> 12:32.150
You're seeing someone.

12:36.957 --> 12:38.957
He told you.

12:41.728 --> 12:43.962
I was sure he wouldn't.

12:45.065 --> 12:46.531
I can never
figure him out.

12:46.533 --> 12:48.066
You think
he's gonna go one way --

12:48.068 --> 12:50.702
turns around,
goes the exact opposite.

12:50.704 --> 12:52.103
Who is she?

12:52.105 --> 12:53.571
[ Sighs ]

12:53.573 --> 12:54.939
Does it matter?
Do you care?

12:54.941 --> 12:56.274
No.

12:57.878 --> 12:59.177
Are you gonna tell me
who she is?

13:01.081 --> 13:02.580
You sound like you care.

13:02.582 --> 13:04.883
I sound practical.

13:04.885 --> 13:07.752
You're dating now.
Fine.

13:07.754 --> 13:09.487
You want to run around with
a bunch of women, good for you.

13:09.489 --> 13:11.289
[ Sighs ]
Play, have an orgy.

13:11.291 --> 13:14.893
Liv, there is
only one woman.

13:14.895 --> 13:16.828
We've been dating
for a while.

13:16.830 --> 13:19.964
♪♪

13:21.067 --> 13:23.067
So, this is serious.

13:25.472 --> 13:27.605
[ Sighs ]

13:27.607 --> 13:29.741
She's special.

13:29.743 --> 13:31.709
You'd like her.

13:35.582 --> 13:38.249
And you don't need to worry
about anything.

13:38.251 --> 13:40.819
She and I are very safe.

13:40.821 --> 13:43.521
