27:17.570 --> 27:18.802
Anchorwoman:
<i> Their approach to sharing --</i>

27:18.804 --> 27:20.471
<i> -...covered under --</i>
<i> -...eclipsed --</i>

27:20.473 --> 27:22.473
<i> -...financial --</i>
<i> -...the ribs for you.</i>

27:22.474 --> 27:24.474
♪<i> I'm never going back</i> ♪
"Frozen"! I love Elsa!

27:24.477 --> 27:28.479
Who doesn't?
♪<i> The past is in the past</i> ♪

27:28.481 --> 27:29.647
You're really good
with kids.

27:29.649 --> 27:31.649
♪<i> Let it go</i> ♪
It's easy.

27:31.651 --> 27:33.283
♪<i> Let it go</i> ♪
You just have to be in touch
with your inner child.

27:33.285 --> 27:35.986
♪<i> And I'll rise</i>
<i> like the break of dawn</i> ♪
And let it go.

27:35.988 --> 27:38.022
♪<i> Let it go, let it --</i> ♪

27:42.862 --> 27:44.595
[ Cellphone chimes, vibrates ]

27:49.468 --> 27:51.101
This damn shooting
in Harrisburg.

27:51.103 --> 27:53.203
I told them
it's not a terrorist attack.

27:54.674 --> 27:56.373
Do you think
he's changed?

27:56.375 --> 27:58.042
Who?

27:58.044 --> 28:00.778
My father. Do you think
he's changed for the better?

28:00.780 --> 28:02.946
Yeah, sure.

28:02.948 --> 28:06.050
Jake, look at me.

28:06.052 --> 28:08.952
Look at me.

28:08.954 --> 28:10.220
I have no compass
with him.

28:10.222 --> 28:12.022
I'm asking you,
has he changed?

28:12.024 --> 28:13.457
I'm not getting in the middle
of you and your daddy issues.

28:13.459 --> 28:14.458
I have to go.

28:14.460 --> 28:15.526
Why did you move in
with him?

28:15.528 --> 28:16.727
What are you two doing
in that house?

28:16.729 --> 28:17.995
I have to go.

28:17.997 --> 28:19.396
Okay,
now you're just interfering

28:19.398 --> 28:20.631
with our national security.

28:20.633 --> 28:21.665
What is it my father wants
from you?

28:21.667 --> 28:23.067
What is he making you do?

28:23.069 --> 28:25.569
Nothing. He doesn't want
anything from me.
No, Jake.

28:25.571 --> 28:27.705
Why do you think he told me
about your new girlfriend?

28:27.707 --> 28:30.407
To get me
to stop seeing you.

28:30.409 --> 28:31.975
He was asking me
to cut you out of my life.

28:31.977 --> 28:33.410
He wants to isolate you,

28:33.412 --> 28:35.512
keep you and me as far apart
as possible.

28:35.514 --> 28:37.014
Because he knows
I'll figure it out,

28:37.016 --> 28:38.649
whatever he's planning,
whatever he's up to.

28:38.651 --> 28:41.151
If I am close enough, then I am
going to figure it out.

28:41.153 --> 28:44.188
If you tell me,
I can help you.

28:44.190 --> 28:47.057
♪♪

28:52.865 --> 28:54.064
[ Cellphone chimes, vibrates ]

29:00.272 --> 29:02.406
I have to go to work.

29:02.408 --> 29:05.476
♪♪

29:14.854 --> 29:16.120
Rachel: The Governor said,
"Let the others go.

29:16.122 --> 29:17.621
Take me.
I'm the one you want."

29:17.623 --> 29:18.856
And he was just so calm.

29:18.858 --> 29:20.290
And then like a minute later,

29:20.292 --> 29:22.593
the guy let everybody go
except for Governor Vargas.

29:22.595 --> 29:24.862
<i> I just hope</i>
<i> he's gonna be okay.</i>

29:24.864 --> 29:26.764
Waters:
<i> If you're just joining us,</i>

29:26.766 --> 29:28.565
<i> there are reports</i>
<i> that just moments ago...</i>
[ Cellphone chiming ]

29:28.567 --> 29:30.968
<i> a gunman entered</i>
<i> the Pennsylvania State Capitol</i>

29:30.970 --> 29:33.871
<i> and at least two Capitol</i>
<i>police officers have been shot.</i>

29:33.873 --> 29:35.672
Abby.

29:36.742 --> 29:38.542
Abby?

29:38.544 --> 29:41.211
Liv, I just wanted...

29:41.213 --> 29:43.413
to...talk.

29:43.415 --> 29:44.948
Right now?

29:44.950 --> 29:46.250
<i> ...where exactly</i>
<i> the governor is,</i>

29:46.252 --> 29:48.619
<i> or whether he's safe.</i>
What's wrong?

29:48.621 --> 29:51.121
Nothing.

29:51.490 --> 29:52.589
Abby?

29:52.591 --> 29:53.757
[ Sighs ] I'm sorry.

29:53.759 --> 29:55.793
I shouldn't have called.

29:55.795 --> 29:58.896
♪♪

30:02.001 --> 30:03.500
What did he do?

30:03.502 --> 30:05.335
That's just it.

30:05.337 --> 30:07.304
You don't want to know.

30:07.306 --> 30:09.740
I shouldn't have called.

30:09.742 --> 30:12.843
♪♪

30:20.252 --> 30:22.119
You're right.
I don't want to know.

30:22.121 --> 30:23.587
I'm sorry.

30:23.589 --> 30:25.889
No, don't be.

30:32.164 --> 30:34.464
Abby...

30:34.466 --> 30:37.034
I-I have to go.
My other line is ringing.

30:37.036 --> 30:40.771
Okay, sure.
Bye.

30:40.773 --> 30:42.372
[ Cellphone beeps ]

30:48.380 --> 30:50.013
[ Sighs ]

30:50.015 --> 30:53.116
♪♪

30:58.557 --> 31:00.324
From what I've gathered,
this hostage taker's

31:00.326 --> 31:01.992
just another disgruntled loner

31:01.994 --> 31:04.127
blaming illegal immigrants
for his personal failures.

31:04.129 --> 31:05.462
So he's not connected
to terrorists,

31:05.464 --> 31:06.463
domestic or otherwise?

31:06.465 --> 31:08.298
He's acting alone.

31:08.300 --> 31:10.901
Well, let's just hope
he doesn't breed copycats.

31:10.903 --> 31:12.469
This will be over soon.

31:12.471 --> 31:13.971
I'm hearing
from my FBI sources

31:13.973 --> 31:15.539
the local SWAT
has sharpshooters in position.

31:15.541 --> 31:18.742
As soon as they get
a clean shot, he's a goner.

31:20.246 --> 31:22.713
Good to hear.

31:22.715 --> 31:25.482
I thought this was our guy.
You told me this was our guy.

31:25.484 --> 31:26.550
He is.

31:26.552 --> 31:28.085
Cyrus:
He's not our guy.

31:28.087 --> 31:30.520
He is our guy. He'll do it.
He'll shoot.

31:30.522 --> 31:33.390
Says what, your spidey sense?
[ Sighs ]

31:33.392 --> 31:35.726
SWAT has sharpshooters
in place.

31:35.728 --> 31:37.160
They're gonna shoot
that incompetent whack job

31:37.162 --> 31:38.528
you recruited.

31:38.530 --> 31:40.731
They're gonna take our
hero moment away from our hero

31:40.733 --> 31:42.266
and give it
to some jackass sharpshooter.

31:42.268 --> 31:44.001
At this point,
there's nothing I can do.

31:44.003 --> 31:46.737
Nothing?! You --
[ Sighs ]

31:46.739 --> 31:48.705
Failure is not one
of your options.

31:48.707 --> 31:49.873
Nothing is impossible.

31:49.875 --> 31:51.608
So you grab your ass
and you get creative

31:51.610 --> 31:53.377
and you do
what needs to be done.

31:53.379 --> 31:57.381
I don't care what it is.
I do not care how you do it.

31:57.383 --> 32:00.250
This is my day.
I am the bride.

32:00.252 --> 32:02.552
So you get me
my hero moment.

32:02.554 --> 32:05.055
And if you don't, you'll go back
into whatever box

32:05.057 --> 32:07.491
you came out of
and you'll stay there.

32:12.464 --> 32:14.865
So what if I am sleeping
with the enemy,

32:14.867 --> 32:16.199
turning a blind eye

32:16.201 --> 32:17.768
to whatever my father is
up to with Jake?

32:17.770 --> 32:19.303
I am<i> choosing.</i>

32:19.305 --> 32:20.304
It's a choice.

32:20.306 --> 32:21.438
I'm playing the game,

32:21.440 --> 32:22.973
and I'm playing it better
than anyone.

32:22.975 --> 32:24.141
And what game
would that be?

32:24.143 --> 32:25.609
What?!
What game would that be?

32:25.611 --> 32:27.744
The one where I win.

32:27.746 --> 32:29.913
You mean the one that requires
all luck and no skill,

32:29.915 --> 32:32.049
no real information
necessary?

32:32.051 --> 32:33.717
I'll be sure
to keep my fingers and toes

32:33.719 --> 32:34.918
crossed for you, Liv.

32:34.920 --> 32:36.453
I have
all the information I need.

32:36.455 --> 32:38.655
You have no real information.
How could you?

32:38.657 --> 32:40.324
When you don't believe there's
any information to collect.

32:40.326 --> 32:42.159
You're not playing
the same game as him.

32:42.161 --> 32:44.227
You're not even
on the same court.
Because I don't want to be!

32:44.229 --> 32:46.063
Because you are that scared
of losing.

32:46.065 --> 32:49.633
Because the only winning move
is not to play!

32:49.635 --> 32:51.601
My father always wins.

32:51.603 --> 32:54.171
He always wins.

32:54.173 --> 32:56.473
You know that
better than anyone.

32:56.475 --> 32:59.343
How many holes
do I have to pull you out of?

32:59.345 --> 33:00.811
So don't lecture.

33:00.813 --> 33:03.680
Don't give me a sermon
like you don't know.

33:05.651 --> 33:07.417
[ Breathes shakily ]

33:07.419 --> 33:10.087
Your guy.
He's coming out.

33:10.089 --> 33:12.122
What? My --

33:12.124 --> 33:13.623
My guy? I don't --

33:13.625 --> 33:16.660
I never considered it before.
But, yeah, you were made.

33:16.662 --> 33:18.628
Just like us.

33:18.630 --> 33:20.430
By him.

33:20.432 --> 33:23.834
Why wouldn't you have
a guy?

33:23.836 --> 33:26.837
He's my<i> father.</i>

33:26.839 --> 33:29.172
<i> My father.</i>

33:29.174 --> 33:32.175
And at the end of the day,
he will always look out for me.

33:32.177 --> 33:34.878
He will always be on my side.
He will always love me.

33:34.880 --> 33:37.547
No.
You don't have a guy.

33:37.549 --> 33:39.850
You don't need one.
You have your father.

33:39.852 --> 33:42.786
He is your guy,
and he is always out.

33:42.788 --> 33:45.222
And you really<i> do</i> need him,

33:45.224 --> 33:47.290
because as long as
he is by your side,

33:47.292 --> 33:49.659
nothing you do
seems bad in comparison.

33:49.661 --> 33:51.028
Your guy is always out,

33:51.030 --> 33:53.397
and he is the biggest,
hungriest monster

33:53.399 --> 33:56.133
on the loosest leash
in the world.

33:56.135 --> 33:58.201
Huck...
A monster
does not change.

33:58.203 --> 34:00.737
A monster is
always hungry.

34:00.739 --> 34:04.408
Do you not understand that
when the monster gets hungry,

34:04.410 --> 34:07.210
he will turn around
and eat you?

34:07.212 --> 34:10.113
♪♪

34:11.817 --> 34:14.317
Listen, it's not too late
to put that gun down

34:14.319 --> 34:15.652
and walk out of here
with your life.

34:15.654 --> 34:17.621
Stop. Talking.

34:21.360 --> 34:24.594
In position.
Hostage visible.

34:24.596 --> 34:27.030
Zero visibility
on the assailant.

34:27.032 --> 34:29.099
Permission to fire
if the target goes live?

34:29.101 --> 34:30.267
Do you have kids?

34:32.738 --> 34:34.504
My daughter's names
are Sara and Anna.

34:34.506 --> 34:36.339
Shut up.

34:36.341 --> 34:40.710
♪♪

34:40.712 --> 34:42.679
[ Gunshot ]

34:42.681 --> 34:45.182
Waters:<i> I repeat, sources on the</i>
<i> scene report what sounded like</i>

34:45.184 --> 34:48.085
<i> a single shot fired at the</i>
<i> Pennsylvania Capitol building</i>

34:48.087 --> 34:50.053
<i> just seconds ago.</i>

34:50.055 --> 34:52.122
<i> It is unknown whether it was</i>
<i> the gunman,</i>

34:52.124 --> 34:54.624
<i> a man named Wayne Turner,</i>
<i> who took the shot,</i>

34:54.626 --> 34:57.694
<i> or a police sniper</i>
<i> firing into the building.</i>

34:57.696 --> 35:01.531
<i> I'm -- I'm sorry.</i>
<i> O-Okay. Right.</i>

35:01.533 --> 35:03.400
<i> Ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i> it appears</i>

35:03.402 --> 35:06.636
<i> Governor Francisco Vargas</i>
<i> has been shot.</i>

35:06.638 --> 35:08.205
<i> But he is alive</i>

35:08.207 --> 35:10.707
<i> and has apparently</i>
<i> overpowered his captor,</i>

35:10.709 --> 35:13.944
<i> who is being apprehended</i>
<i>by Harrisburg SWAT as we speak.</i>

35:13.946 --> 35:15.612
Cut to footage.
<i> But...</i>

35:15.614 --> 35:17.414
Cut to footage, cut to footage,
cut to the damn footage.

35:17.416 --> 35:19.282
<i> ...we apparently have footage</i>

35:19.284 --> 35:21.384
<i> of Governor Vargas's</i>
<i> heroic act.</i>

35:21.386 --> 35:24.121
<i> We're gonna cut to that</i>
<i> right now.</i>

35:24.123 --> 35:25.388
<i> Take a look.</i>

35:25.390 --> 35:28.792
♪♪

35:28.794 --> 35:30.460
[<i> Gunshot</i> ]

35:36.502 --> 35:38.568
<i> Unbelievable images</i>
<i> this evening.</i>

35:38.570 --> 35:40.303
<i> The heroic and selfless stand</i>

35:40.305 --> 35:42.506
<i> made by</i>
<i> Governor Francisco Vargas.</i>

35:42.508 --> 35:43.840
<i> If you hadn't heard</i>
<i> of Francisco Vargas</i>

35:43.842 --> 35:45.609
<i> before tonight,</i>

35:45.611 --> 35:47.878
<i> then you will certainly know</i>
<i> him by tomorrow morning.</i>

35:56.855 --> 35:58.588
Man: Back it up, everyone.
This side of the tape.

35:58.590 --> 36:00.590
Here comes Vargas now,
as you can see.

36:00.592 --> 36:02.592
[<i> Indistinct conversations</i> ]

36:02.594 --> 36:05.762
This was the scene last night
in Harrisburg, Pennsylvania,

36:05.764 --> 36:09.599
where Governor Francisco Vargas
disarmed a deranged gunman

36:09.601 --> 36:13.436
in an act that many refer to now
simply as "the tackle."

36:13.438 --> 36:15.305
<i>Here's what one of the hostages</i>
<i> had to say</i>

36:15.307 --> 36:17.040
<i> about the governor last night.</i>
Abby.

36:17.042 --> 36:18.341
Rachel:
<i> The governor was incredible.</i>

36:18.343 --> 36:20.343
<i> He said, "Let the others go.</i>

36:20.345 --> 36:21.778
<i> Take me.</i>
<i> I'm the one you want."</i>

36:21.780 --> 36:23.446
It never gets old.
<i> He was just so calm.</i>

36:23.448 --> 36:24.981
[ Clears throat ]
<i>And then like a minute later...</i>

36:24.983 --> 36:26.716
What?
<i> ...the guy let</i>
<i> everybody else go</i>

36:26.718 --> 36:28.351
<i> except for Governor Vargas.</i>

36:28.353 --> 36:29.853
Oh!

36:29.855 --> 36:31.888
Abby: It's the private entrance
to the residence.

36:31.890 --> 36:33.890
<i> Your</i> residence.

36:33.892 --> 36:36.126
I'll say
we were discussing a story.

36:36.128 --> 36:38.728
In bed?
Look at her hair.

36:38.730 --> 36:41.198
Abby, I told you --
my personal life is personal.

36:41.200 --> 36:43.233
Not this time, it isn't.
This time, it's political.

36:43.235 --> 36:44.901
Is the President
of the United States

36:44.903 --> 36:46.803
getting laid
while a mass murderer

36:46.805 --> 36:49.072
roamed the halls of
the Pennsylvania State Capitol?

36:49.074 --> 36:50.540
I hadn't been made aware
of that yet.

36:50.542 --> 36:51.875
Doesn't matter.
That's how they'll spin it.

36:51.877 --> 36:53.510
You know that.
I know that you know that.

36:53.512 --> 36:55.312
Don't play dumb.
Okay. That's enough of --

36:55.314 --> 36:57.147
Do you think
that I like this?

36:57.149 --> 36:59.049
I don't like this any more
than you do, Mr. President.

36:59.051 --> 37:00.984
Do you think I ever want to walk
into a room and say

37:00.986 --> 37:02.385
"Did you wear a condom,
sir?"

37:02.387 --> 37:04.221
Abby.
"Is your DNA inside of her?"

37:04.223 --> 37:06.990
Abby!
These are the questions
that I do not ever want to ask.

37:06.992 --> 37:08.825
And unless we have
an understanding,

37:08.827 --> 37:10.727
protocols, a system,

37:10.729 --> 37:12.562
these are things I need to know
to protect you.

37:12.564 --> 37:14.231
I am<i> trying</i>
to protect you.

37:14.233 --> 37:16.166
And it's awful
that I have to do this,

37:16.168 --> 37:18.368
that we have to do this,
but this is where we are now.

37:18.370 --> 37:20.403
A year from now,
you will be a free man

37:20.405 --> 37:22.205
and you can rejoin
the living

37:22.207 --> 37:23.740
and you can cavort
with anyone you want,

37:23.742 --> 37:25.408
anywhere you want,
in any way that you want,

37:25.410 --> 37:27.244
and I guarantee

37:27.246 --> 37:28.545
that I will never,
ever interrupt you.

37:28.547 --> 37:31.081
But until then,
we're here now,

37:31.083 --> 37:32.515
and you know this is
how it has to be.

37:32.517 --> 37:34.117
So please don't fight me
on this anymore.

37:34.119 --> 37:37.087
And stop threatening
to fire me, sir.

37:37.089 --> 37:38.355
Either do it
or don't do it.

37:38.357 --> 37:40.257
But I will not be
threatened again.

37:40.259 --> 37:41.258
You want to fire me?

37:41.260 --> 37:42.759
Fire me right now,
Mr. President.

37:49.468 --> 37:52.269
Fitz.

37:52.271 --> 37:54.604
We should at least be
on a first-name basis.

37:54.606 --> 37:56.806
Because if I have to tell you
about my sex life,

37:56.808 --> 38:00.744
that officially makes you
my closest friend in the world.

38:00.746 --> 38:02.746
Fitz.

38:02.748 --> 38:04.781
Okay.

38:04.783 --> 38:06.850
Thank you, Abby.

38:08.987 --> 38:10.954
You're welcome...

38:10.956 --> 38:13.423
Fitz.

38:13.425 --> 38:16.126
♪♪

38:19.564 --> 38:22.999
[ Cellphone rings ]

38:24.770 --> 38:26.069
Susan: Answer it.

38:26.071 --> 38:27.270
No.
It's okay.

38:27.272 --> 38:29.005
You should answer it.
It keeps ringing.

38:29.007 --> 38:30.473
It's just work.
It's not important.

38:30.475 --> 38:32.575
[ Laughs ]
Your work is always important.

38:32.577 --> 38:33.977
You're the Attorney General
of the United States.

38:33.979 --> 38:36.846
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

38:37.849 --> 38:38.848
Hello?

38:38.850 --> 38:40.116
How was it?

38:40.118 --> 38:41.818
Can we talk later?

38:41.820 --> 38:43.453
Wait.
She's still there?

38:43.455 --> 38:45.989
Yes, we're waiting
on the verdict.

38:45.991 --> 38:49.092
♪♪

38:51.963 --> 38:54.597
[ Indistinct conversations ]

38:55.000 --> 38:56.099
Abby!

38:56.101 --> 38:57.701
Work wife is hard.

38:57.703 --> 38:59.669
Very high divorce rate.
Still the Lillian thing?

38:59.671 --> 39:01.137
You know about the picture?

39:01.139 --> 39:02.272
There's a picture.

39:02.274 --> 39:04.207
And I'm gonna get devoured
in the briefing.

39:04.209 --> 39:06.309
This isn't going away,
and you have been gone,

39:06.311 --> 39:07.944
and I know you are
grieving your cousin...

39:07.946 --> 39:10.280
Uh, it's difficult.

39:10.282 --> 39:13.283
...but I have to say it is not
easy around here without you.

39:13.285 --> 39:15.652
Red, you know I'd never tell you
how to do your job.

39:15.654 --> 39:18.955
Oh, yes, you would.

39:18.957 --> 39:20.590
Do it. Please.

39:22.361 --> 39:25.328
If you can't beat him,
distract him.

39:25.330 --> 39:27.163
Get what's his face
from the Harrisburg thing

39:27.165 --> 39:29.232
into the Oval
for a meet-and-greet.

39:29.234 --> 39:31.201
At least,
that's what I'd do.

39:31.203 --> 39:32.736
Thank you.

39:32.738 --> 39:35.105
Everyone loves a hero.

39:38.744 --> 39:41.578
Everyone loves a hero.

39:41.580 --> 39:44.814
♪♪

39:45.484 --> 39:47.083
Okay, kiddo.
It's go time.

39:47.085 --> 39:48.685
You walk in there
and tell them your name.

39:48.687 --> 39:50.086
Wait, you're not coming?

39:50.088 --> 39:51.187
I can't, buddy.

39:51.189 --> 39:52.655
Just go in
and tell them who you are

39:52.657 --> 39:54.057
and that you need to
find your mom,

39:54.059 --> 39:55.058
and they'll take it
from there.

39:55.060 --> 39:56.526
You can handle this,
right, champ?

39:56.528 --> 39:57.894
Sure.

39:57.896 --> 39:59.763
See you later, Max.

39:59.765 --> 40:02.499
See you later,
Uncle Charlie.

40:04.035 --> 40:05.568
Oh. Okay.

40:08.039 --> 40:09.038
Get out of here.

40:09.040 --> 40:11.040
Okay.

40:11.042 --> 40:14.444
♪♪

40:15.580 --> 40:17.847
Tom: Most parents,
their child gets in trouble,

40:17.849 --> 40:19.883
faces death,
they pray to God and say,

40:19.885 --> 40:21.017
"God, take me instead.

40:21.019 --> 40:23.086
Spare my baby.
Let them live."

40:23.088 --> 40:25.388
Are you one
of those parents, Wayne?

40:25.390 --> 40:27.490
Willing to sacrifice
your life for theirs?

40:30.762 --> 40:32.829
Yes or no.

40:34.566 --> 40:36.466
Yes.

40:36.468 --> 40:38.301
Hey, it's me.

40:38.303 --> 40:39.369
The package
you wanted delivered --

40:39.371 --> 40:40.603
It's in the mail.

40:40.605 --> 40:42.539
Thanks.

40:42.541 --> 40:44.808
The money will be in
your account within the hour.

40:46.411 --> 40:48.411
I'm back.
I know, I know.

40:48.413 --> 40:50.580
Mini-vacays are totally
not a thing around here.

40:50.582 --> 40:52.148
Shame me all you want.
I deserve it.

40:52.150 --> 40:53.450
I hope it was worth it.

40:53.452 --> 40:55.385
Um, God, it totally was.

40:55.387 --> 40:59.789
Charlie and I ended up --
we -- we babysat a kid.

40:59.791 --> 41:02.225
And it was fantastic.

41:02.227 --> 41:04.394
If you say so.

41:04.396 --> 41:05.895
God,
I never thought I'd say it,

41:05.897 --> 41:08.498
but Charlie is going to make
an awesome dad.

41:08.500 --> 41:11.000
Where's Liv?

41:11.002 --> 41:13.036
Right here.
Huck, Quinn, come with me.

41:16.675 --> 41:18.641
Don't mind me.
I just work here.

41:18.643 --> 41:20.343
Vanessa Moss.

41:20.345 --> 41:21.845
I need a complete
background check,

41:21.847 --> 41:24.447
a full surveillance
at both home and office,

41:24.449 --> 41:26.516
a list of all property
holdings, past and present.

41:26.518 --> 41:28.585
I need information --
real information.

41:28.587 --> 41:30.353
Are we clear on what game
we're playing here?

41:30.355 --> 41:31.855
Absolutely.

41:31.857 --> 41:33.990
Wait. Who is this?
Who is Vanessa Moss?

41:33.992 --> 41:35.058
The woman Jake is seeing.

41:36.094 --> 41:38.027
Wait.
This is what we're doing?

41:38.029 --> 41:39.028
We're spying on Jake?

41:40.499 --> 41:41.431
Yes.

41:41.433 --> 41:44.868
♪♪

41:44.870 --> 41:46.936
[ Door opens ]

41:48.273 --> 41:50.440
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

41:50.442 --> 41:53.710
♪♪

41:58.683 --> 42:01.885
Cyrus...[Clears throat]
this is Governor Vargas.

42:01.887 --> 42:03.887
Governor Vargas, Cyrus Beene.
White House Chief of Staff.

42:03.889 --> 42:05.522
It's a pleasure to meet you,
Mr. Beene.

42:05.524 --> 42:08.525
The pleasure is all mine,
Governor. I assure you.

42:08.527 --> 42:10.793
Abby: Okay.
Right this way, Governor.

42:10.795 --> 42:13.530
Thank you, sir.
Hmm.

